==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''soft sawder''' ''(uncountable)''

#[[cajole|Cajoling]] or [[flattery]].
#*"If she goes to act ugly, I'll give her a dose of "'''soft sawder'''"; that will take the frown out of her [[frontispiece]]...!" &mdash;[[w:Thomas Haliburton|Thomas Haliburton]], "The Trotting Horse" (1836) &mdash; first usage
#*"How the old boy swallowed my '''soft sawder''' and [[Brummagem]] notes!" &mdash;[[w:Tom Taylor|Tom Taylor]], ''[[wikisource:The Ticket-of-Leave Man|The Ticket-of-Leave Man]]'' (1863)

===Etymology===
Phonetic spelling of "soft [[solder]]"; that is, solder that melts at a lower temperature.

